<p>I am trying to create a simple star rating input via angular ui-bootstrap. The code works fine except that the <code>ng-model</code> is not grabbing the value from the model.</p>  <p>Here is the markup:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div ng-controller="shopperFeedbackController"&gt;         &lt;div class="row feedback-rating-row" &gt;             &lt;div class="col-sm-16"&gt;                 &lt;div class="feedback-label"&gt;                     Rating:                 &lt;/div&gt;                  &lt;div class="feedback-rating-star-input"&gt;                     &lt;rating ng-model="rate" &lt;--- Not working                             max="max_rating"                              on-hover="hovering_over(value)"                              on-leave="overStar = null"                              titles="['one','two','three']" &gt;                     &lt;/rating&gt;                 &lt;/div&gt;             &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>And the code:</p>  <pre><code>snbApp.controller('shopperFeedbackController', function ($scope) {   $scope.max_rating = 5;   $scope.rate = 3; }); </code></pre>